{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"My mission in life since I was a kid was,"},{"time":3000,"text":"and is, to take the rest of you into space."},{"time":6000,"text":"It's during our lifetime that we're going to take the Earth,"},{"time":10000,"text":"take the people of Earth and transition off, permanently. And that's exciting."},{"time":14000,"text":"In fact, I think it is a moral imperative"},{"time":16000,"text":"that we open the space frontier."},{"time":19000,"text":"You know, it's the first time that we're going to have a chance"},{"time":21000,"text":"to have planetary redundancy,"},{"time":23000,"text":"a chance to, if you would, back up the biosphere."},{"time":26000,"text":"And if you think about space,"},{"time":29000,"text":"everything we hold of value on this planet --"},{"time":32000,"text":"metals and minerals and real estate and energy -- is in infinite quantities in space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36000,"text":"In fact, the Earth is a crumb in a supermarket filled with resources."},{"time":41000,"text":"The analogy for me is Alaska. You know, we bought Alaska."},{"time":44000,"text":"We Americans bought Alaska in the 1850s. It's called Seward's folly."},{"time":48000,"text":"We valued it as the number of seal pelts we could kill."},{"time":52000,"text":"And then we discovered these things -- gold and oil and fishing and timber --"},{"time":56000,"text":"and it became, you know, a trillion-dollar economy,"},{"time":59000,"text":"and now we take our honeymoons there. The same thing will happen in space."},{"time":62000,"text":"We are on the verge of the greatest exploration"},{"time":65000,"text":"that the human race has ever known."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67000,"text":"We explore for three reasons,"},{"time":69000,"text":"the weakest of which is curiosity."},{"time":71000,"text":"You know, it's funded NASA's budget up until now."},{"time":75000,"text":"Some images from Mars, 1997."},{"time":78000,"text":"In fact, I think in the next decade, without any question,"},{"time":80000,"text":"we will discover life on Mars and find that it is literally ubiquitous"},{"time":84000,"text":"under the soils and different parts of that planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":87000,"text":"The stronger motivator, the much stronger motivator, is fear."},{"time":90000,"text":"It drove us to the moon. We -- literally in fear -- with the Soviet Union"},{"time":94000,"text":"raced to the moon. And we have these huge rocks,"},{"time":98000,"text":"you know, killer-sized rocks in the hundreds of thousands or millions out there,"},{"time":103000,"text":"and while the probability is very small,"},{"time":105000,"text":"the impact, figured in literally,"},{"time":107000,"text":"of one of these hitting the Earth is so huge"},{"time":110000,"text":"that to spend a small fraction looking, searching,"},{"time":113000,"text":"preparing to defend, is not unreasonable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115000,"text":"And of course, the third motivator,"},{"time":117000,"text":"one near and dear to my heart as an entrepreneur, is wealth."},{"time":121000,"text":"In fact, the greatest wealth. If you think about these other asteroids,"},{"time":125000,"text":"there's a class of the nickel iron,"},{"time":127000,"text":"which in platinum-group metal markets alone"},{"time":129000,"text":"are worth something like 20 trillion dollars,"},{"time":131000,"text":"if you can go out and grab one of these rocks."},{"time":133000,"text":"My plan is to actually buy puts on the precious metal market,"},{"time":136000,"text":"and then actually claim that I'm going to go out and get one."},{"time":138000,"text":"And that will fund the actual mission to go and get one."},{"time":141000,"text":"But fear, curiosity and greed have driven us."},{"time":144000,"text":"And for me, this is -- I'm the short kid on the right."},{"time":148000,"text":"This was -- my motivation was actually during Apollo."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152000,"text":"And Apollo was one of the greatest motivators ever."},{"time":154000,"text":"If you think about what happened at the turn of -- early 1960s,"},{"time":160000,"text":"on May 25, JFK said, \"We're going to go to the moon.\""},{"time":164000,"text":"And people left their jobs and they went to obscure locations"},{"time":167000,"text":"to go and be part of this amazing mission."},{"time":170000,"text":"And we knew nothing about going to space."},{"time":172000,"text":"We went from having literally put Alan Shepard in suborbital flight"},{"time":175000,"text":"to going to the moon in eight years,"},{"time":177000,"text":"and the average age of the people that got us there was 26 years old."},{"time":183000,"text":"They didn't know what couldn't be done."},{"time":184000,"text":"They had to make up everything."},{"time":187000,"text":"And that, my friend, is amazing motivation."},{"time":189000,"text":"This is Gene Cernan, a good friend of mine, saying,"},{"time":192000,"text":"\"If I can go to the moon\" -- this is the last human on the moon so far --"},{"time":196000,"text":"\"nothing, nothing is impossible.\" But of course,"},{"time":199000,"text":"we've thought about the government always as the person taking us there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203000,"text":"But I put forward here, the government is not going to get us there."},{"time":207000,"text":"The government is unable to take the risks required to open up this precious frontier."},{"time":212000,"text":"The shuttle is costing a billion dollars a launch."},{"time":214000,"text":"That's a pathetic number. It's unreasonable."},{"time":217000,"text":"We shouldn't be happy in standing for that."},{"time":220000,"text":"One of the things that we did with the Ansari X PRIZE"},{"time":222000,"text":"was take the challenge on that risk is OK, you know."},{"time":226000,"text":"As we are going out there and taking on a new frontier,"},{"time":229000,"text":"we should be allowed to risk."},{"time":231000,"text":"In fact, anyone who says we shouldn't, you know,"},{"time":234000,"text":"just needs to be put aside, because, as we go forward,"},{"time":238000,"text":"in fact, the greatest discoveries we will ever know is ahead of us."},{"time":242000,"text":"The entrepreneurs in the space business are the furry mammals,"},{"time":245000,"text":"and clearly the industrial-military complex --"},{"time":247000,"text":"with Boeing and Lockheed and NASA -- are the dinosaurs."},{"time":251000,"text":"The ability for us to access these resources"},{"time":254000,"text":"to gain planetary redundancy --"},{"time":256000,"text":"we can now gather all the information, the genetic codes,"},{"time":259000,"text":"you know, everything stored on our databases,"},{"time":261000,"text":"and back them up off the planet,"},{"time":263000,"text":"in case there would be one of those disastrous situations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":267000,"text":"The difficulty is getting there, and clearly, the cost to orbit is key."},{"time":272000,"text":"Once you're in orbit, you are two thirds of the way, energetically, to anywhere --"},{"time":275000,"text":"the moon, to Mars. And today,"},{"time":278000,"text":"there's only three vehicles -- the U.S. shuttle, the Russian Soyuz"},{"time":282000,"text":"and the Chinese vehicle -- that gets you there."},{"time":284000,"text":"Arguably, it's about 100 million dollars a person on the space shuttle."},{"time":289000,"text":"One of the companies I started, Space Adventures, will sell you a ticket."},{"time":292000,"text":"We've done two so far. We'll be announcing two more on the Soyuz"},{"time":296000,"text":"to go up to the space station for 20 million dollars."},{"time":299000,"text":"But that's expensive and to understand what the potential is --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":303000,"text":"(Laughter) --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":305000,"text":"it is expensive. But people are willing to pay that!"},{"time":308000,"text":"You know, one -- we have a very unique period in time today."},{"time":311000,"text":"For the first time ever, we have enough wealth"},{"time":313000,"text":"concentrated in the hands of few individuals"},{"time":315000,"text":"and the technology accessible"},{"time":317000,"text":"that will allow us to really drive space exploration."},{"time":321000,"text":"But how cheap could it get? I want to give you the end point."},{"time":325000,"text":"We know -- 20 million dollars today, you can go and buy a ticket,"},{"time":327000,"text":"but how cheap could it get?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":329000,"text":"Let's go back to high school physics here."},{"time":330000,"text":"If you calculate the amount of potential energy, mgh,"},{"time":334000,"text":"to take you and your spacesuit up to a couple hundred miles,"},{"time":337000,"text":"and then you accelerate yourself to 17,500 miles per hour --"},{"time":341000,"text":"remember, that one half MV squared -- and you figure it out."},{"time":345000,"text":"It's about 5.7 gigajoules of energy."},{"time":349000,"text":"If you expended that over an hour, it's about 1.6 megawatts."},{"time":354000,"text":"If you go to one of Vijay's micro-power sources,"},{"time":357000,"text":"and they sell it to you for seven cents a kilowatt hour --"},{"time":359000,"text":"anybody here fast in math?"},{"time":361000,"text":"How much will it cost you and your spacesuit to go to orbit?"},{"time":365000,"text":"100 bucks. That's the price-improvement curve that --"},{"time":369000,"text":"we need some breakthroughs in physics along the way,"},{"time":371000,"text":"I'll grant you that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":374000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":375000,"text":"But guys, if history has taught us anything,"},{"time":379000,"text":"it's that if you can imagine it, you will get there eventually."},{"time":382000,"text":"I have no question that the physics,"},{"time":385000,"text":"the engineering to get us down to the point"},{"time":388000,"text":"where all of us can afford orbital space flight is around the corner."},{"time":392000,"text":"The difficulty is that there needs to be a real marketplace to drive the investment."},{"time":397000,"text":"Today, the Boeings and the Lockheeds don't spend a dollar"},{"time":401000,"text":"of their own money in R&amp;D."},{"time":403000,"text":"It's all government research dollars, and very few of those."},{"time":406000,"text":"And in fact, the large corporations,"},{"time":408000,"text":"the governments, can't take the risk."},{"time":410000,"text":"So we need what I call an exothermic economic reaction in space."},{"time":414000,"text":"Today's commercial markets worldwide, global commercial launch market?"},{"time":418000,"text":"12 to 15 launches per year."},{"time":421000,"text":"Number of commercial companies out there? 12 to 15 companies."},{"time":423000,"text":"One per company. That's not it. There's only one marketplace,"},{"time":427000,"text":"and I call them self-loading carbon payloads."},{"time":430000,"text":"They come with their own money. They're easy to make."},{"time":433000,"text":"It's people. The Ansari X PRIZE was my solution,"},{"time":437000,"text":"reading about Lindbergh for creating the vehicles to get us there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":441000,"text":"We offered 10 million dollars in cash for the first reusable ship,"},{"time":444000,"text":"carry three people up to 100 kilometers,"},{"time":446000,"text":"come back down, and within two weeks, make the trip again."},{"time":449000,"text":"Twenty-six teams from seven countries entered the competition,"},{"time":453000,"text":"spending between one to 25 million dollars each."},{"time":456000,"text":"And of course, we had beautiful SpaceShipOne,"},{"time":458000,"text":"which made those two flights and won the competition."},{"time":462000,"text":"And I'd like to take you there, to that morning,"},{"time":465000,"text":"for just a quick video."}]},{"cues":[{"time":483000,"text":"(Video) Pilot: Release our fire."}]},{"cues":[{"time":488000,"text":"Richard Searfoss: Good luck."}]},{"cues":[{"time":493000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":508000,"text":"RS: We've got an altitude call of 368,000 feet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":516000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":519000,"text":"RS: So in my official capacity as the chief judge"},{"time":522000,"text":"of the Ansari X PRIZE competition,"},{"time":524000,"text":"I declare that Mojave Aerospace Ventures"},{"time":526000,"text":"has indeed earned the Ansari X PRIZE."}]},{"cues":[{"time":529000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":531000,"text":"Peter Diamandis: Probably the most difficult thing that I had to do"},{"time":533000,"text":"was raise the capital for this. It was literally impossible."},{"time":536000,"text":"We went -- I went to 100, 200 CEOs, CMOs."},{"time":540000,"text":"No one believed it was done. Everyone said, \"Oh, what does NASA think?"},{"time":542000,"text":"Well, people are going to die,"},{"time":544000,"text":"how can you possibly going to put this forward?\""},{"time":546000,"text":"I found a visionary family, the Ansari family, and Champ Car,"},{"time":549000,"text":"and raised part of the money, but not the full 10 million."}]},{"cues":[{"time":552000,"text":"And what I ended up doing was going out to the insurance industry"},{"time":556000,"text":"and buying a hole-in-one insurance policy."},{"time":558000,"text":"See, the insurance companies went to Boeing and Lockheed,"},{"time":560000,"text":"and said, \"Are you going to compete?\" No."},{"time":562000,"text":"\"Are you going to compete?\" No. \"No one's going to win this thing.\""},{"time":564000,"text":"So, they took a bet that no one would win by January of '05,"},{"time":569000,"text":"and I took a bet that someone would win."}]},{"cues":[{"time":573000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":574000,"text":"So -- and the best thing is they paid off and the check didn't bounce."}]},{"cues":[{"time":580000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":581000,"text":"We've had a lot of accomplishments"},{"time":583000,"text":"and it's been a tremendous success."},{"time":585000,"text":"One of the things I'm most happy about is that the SpaceShipOne"},{"time":591000,"text":"is going to hang in Air and Space Museum,"},{"time":593000,"text":"next to the Spirit of St. Louis and the Wright Flyer."},{"time":595000,"text":"Isn't that great? (Applause)"},{"time":600000,"text":"So a little bit about the future, steps to space, what's available for you."},{"time":604000,"text":"Today, you can go and experience weightless flights."},{"time":608000,"text":"By '08, suborbital flights, the price tag for that, you know, on Virgin,"},{"time":612000,"text":"is going to be about 200,000."},{"time":614000,"text":"There are three or four other serious efforts that will bring the price down very rapidly,"},{"time":617000,"text":"I think, to about 25,000 dollars for a suborbital flight."},{"time":621000,"text":"Orbital flights -- we can take you to the space station."}]},{"cues":[{"time":623000,"text":"And then I truly believe, once a group is in orbit around the Earth --"},{"time":627000,"text":"I know if they don't do it, I am --"},{"time":629000,"text":"we're going to stockpile some fuel,"},{"time":631000,"text":"make a beeline for the moon and grab some real estate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":635000,"text":"Quick moment for the designers in the audience."},{"time":638000,"text":"We spent 11 years getting FAA approval to do zero gravity flights."},{"time":642000,"text":"Here are some fun images. Here's Burt Rutan"},{"time":644000,"text":"and my good friend Greg Meronek inside a zero gravity --"},{"time":648000,"text":"people think a zero gravity room,"},{"time":650000,"text":"there's a switch on there that turns it off --"},{"time":652000,"text":"but it's actually parabolic flight of an airplane."},{"time":654000,"text":"And turns out 7-Up has just done a little commercial that's airing this month."},{"time":659000,"text":"If we can get the audio up?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":661000,"text":"(Video) Narrator: For a chance to win the first free ticket to space,"},{"time":665000,"text":"look for specially marked packages of Diet 7-Up."},{"time":669000,"text":"When you want the taste that won't weigh you down,"},{"time":671000,"text":"the only way to go is up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":673000,"text":"PD: That was filmed inside our airplane, and so, you can now do this."},{"time":678000,"text":"We're based down in Florida."},{"time":680000,"text":"Let me talk about the other thing I'm excited about."},{"time":682000,"text":"The future of prizes. You know, prizes are a very old idea."},{"time":686000,"text":"I had the pleasure of borrowing from the Longitude Prize"},{"time":689000,"text":"and the Orteig Prize that put Lindbergh forward."},{"time":692000,"text":"And we have made a decision in the X PRIZE Foundation"},{"time":695000,"text":"to actually carry that concept forward into other technology areas,"},{"time":699000,"text":"and we just took on a new mission statement:"},{"time":701000,"text":"\"to bring about radical breakthroughs in space"},{"time":704000,"text":"and other technologies for the benefit of humanity.\""},{"time":707000,"text":"And this is something that we're very excited about."},{"time":710000,"text":"I showed this slide to Larry Page, who just joined our board."}]},{"cues":[{"time":713000,"text":"And you know, when you give to a nonprofit,"},{"time":715000,"text":"you might have 50 cents on the dollar."},{"time":717000,"text":"If you have a matching grant, it's typically two or three to one."},{"time":720000,"text":"If you put up a prize, you can get literally a 50 to one leverage on your dollars."},{"time":725000,"text":"And that's huge. And then he turned around and said,"},{"time":727000,"text":"\"Well, if you back a prize institute that runs a 10 prize, you get 500 to one.\""},{"time":731000,"text":"I said, \"Well, that's great.\""},{"time":733000,"text":"So, we have actually -- are looking to turn the X PRIZE"},{"time":736000,"text":"into a world-class prize institute."},{"time":739000,"text":"This is what happens when you put up a prize,"},{"time":742000,"text":"when you announce it and teams start to begin doing trials."},{"time":746000,"text":"You get publicity increase, and when it's won,"},{"time":749000,"text":"publicity shoots through the roof -- if it's properly managed --"},{"time":751000,"text":"and that's part of the benefits to a sponsor."},{"time":755000,"text":"Then, when the prize is actually won, after it's moving,"},{"time":759000,"text":"you get societal benefits, you know, new technology, new capability."},{"time":763000,"text":"And the benefit to the sponsors"},{"time":765000,"text":"is the sum of the publicity and societal benefits over the long term."},{"time":768000,"text":"That's our value proposition in a prize."}]},{"cues":[{"time":771000,"text":"If you were going to go and try to create SpaceShipOne,"},{"time":773000,"text":"or any kind of a new technology,"},{"time":775000,"text":"you have to fund that from the beginning"},{"time":778000,"text":"and maintain that funding with an uncertain outcome."},{"time":781000,"text":"It may or may not happen. But if you put up a prize,"},{"time":784000,"text":"the beautiful thing is, you know, it's a very small maintenance fee,"},{"time":787000,"text":"and you pay on success."},{"time":789000,"text":"Orteig didn't pay a dime out to the nine teams that went across --"},{"time":791000,"text":"tried to go across the Atlantic,"},{"time":793000,"text":"and we didn't pay a dime until someone won the Ansari X PRIZE."},{"time":796000,"text":"So, prizes work great."},{"time":798000,"text":"You know, innovators, the entrepreneurs out there,"},{"time":800000,"text":"you know that when you're going for a goal,"},{"time":802000,"text":"the first thing you have to do is believe"},{"time":804000,"text":"that you can do it yourself."},{"time":806000,"text":"Then, you've got to, you know, face potential public ridicule"},{"time":808000,"text":"of -- that's a crazy idea, it'll never work."},{"time":810000,"text":"And then you have to convince others,"},{"time":813000,"text":"so that they can, in fact, help you raise the funds,"},{"time":816000,"text":"and then you've got to deal with the fact that you've got government bureaucracies"},{"time":819000,"text":"and institutions that don't want you to move those things forward,"},{"time":822000,"text":"and you have to deal with failures. What a prize does,"},{"time":824000,"text":"what we've experienced a prize doing,"},{"time":826000,"text":"is literally help to short-circuit or support all of these things,"},{"time":831000,"text":"because a prize credentials the idea that this is a good idea."},{"time":833000,"text":"Well, it must be a good idea."},{"time":835000,"text":"Someone's offering 10 million dollars to go and do this thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":838000,"text":"And each of these areas was something that we found"},{"time":841000,"text":"the Ansari X PRIZE helped short-circuit these for innovation."},{"time":846000,"text":"So, as an organization, we put together a prize discovery process"},{"time":849000,"text":"of how to come up with prizes and write the rules,"},{"time":852000,"text":"and we're actually looking at creating prizes"},{"time":855000,"text":"in a number of different categories."},{"time":857000,"text":"We're looking at attacking energy, environment, nanotechnology --"},{"time":862000,"text":"and I'll talk about those more in a moment."},{"time":864000,"text":"And the way we're doing that is we're creating prize teams"},{"time":866000,"text":"within the X PRIZE. We have a space prize team."},{"time":869000,"text":"We're going after an orbital prize."}]},{"cues":[{"time":871000,"text":"We are looking at a number of energy prizes."},{"time":874000,"text":"Craig Venter has just joined our board"},{"time":876000,"text":"and we're doing a rapid genome sequencing prize with him,"},{"time":878000,"text":"we'll be announcing later this fall,"},{"time":880000,"text":"about -- imagine being able to sequence anybody's DNA"},{"time":884000,"text":"for under 1,000 dollars, revolutionize medicine."},{"time":887000,"text":"And clean water, education, medicine and even looking at social entrepreneurship."},{"time":892000,"text":"So my final slide here is, the most critical tool"},{"time":895000,"text":"for solving humanity's grand challenges -- it isn't technology,"},{"time":899000,"text":"it isn't money, it's only one thing --"},{"time":901000,"text":"it's the committed, passionate human mind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":904000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}